// @ok
// Soundness corpus index (ROADMAP A12).
//
// This directory pins down VL's type-safety contract: every well-typed program
// is type-safe at runtime (see docs/soundness.md). Each file is a small, focused
// "must-error" or "must-not-error" program so a future deep change to inference,
// narrowing, or codegen cannot silently regress soundness — a regression flips a
// `@error` to `@ok` (or vice versa) and breaks `deno task test`.
//
// Conventions used here:
//   // @ok   — compiles with zero ERROR diagnostics, NOT instantiated/run
//             (the "must-not-error", type-level half of the contract)
//   // @run  — compiles AND runs; `@log` lines assert the narrowing actually
//             produced the right runtime value (sound use end to end)
//   // @error / @error-at — the "must-error" half: an unsound use is rejected
//
// KNOWN-UNSOUND corners are filed as `xfail-*.vl` with a `TODO(soundness):` note
// and a `@ok` directive: they encode a gap that is documented but not yet
// enforced (e.g. the permissive arithmetic hole-operand rule, ROADMAP A13).
//
// This file is itself a trivial `@ok` so the directory is never empty.
let _corpus = 0
